</p><p class="- topic/p "> The test shows which media settings are used on the print. All prints work independent of the non-installed license options. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">You can choose to print: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">PQT Matte Specialty (8 pass) 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">PQT Gloss Specialty (8 pass) 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">PQT White Specialty (8/12 Pass) 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Flush print CMYK 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Flush print cyan 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Flush print magenta 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Flush print black 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Flush print yellow 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Flush print white 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Matte-Gloss print (test print for FLXfinish+) 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Mirror position verification (mirror position verification for FLXfinish+) 
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p ">The Flush Print(s) prints an about 70 cm long print with the selected color in a specific coverage per color with is completely cured. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The test prints are automatically printed multiple times. It can be aborted any time. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Goal of the print is to refresh the ink of the printhead (expired ink). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">To flush the complete ink of the printhead the flush test needs to finish without aborting. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Flush print details: 
